ce:section.ce:para:
Pre-designed patterns were printed onto an off-white (unbleached) cellulose paper sheets using a conventional printer attached to the computer. The printed photos showed a visible and brilliant blue fluorescence under irradiation with UV light (
                        Fig. 9

                        ). Because of its advantageous characteristics, such as cheap cost, environmental friendliness, ease of preparation, and ease of use, the current N-CDs fluorescent ink has the potential to be used in printing for the purpose of storing and encrypting information. The blank paper document showed a dark off-white backdrop that boosted the treated papers' optical photo-switchable performance to blue color. Bleached white surfaces do not show the same degree of fluorescence to the human eye as the darker ones, such as off-white paper sheets, where the resultant blue color under UV light is readily evident. All printed paper document displayed rapid and reversible photo-switchable fluorescent performance under UV irradiation.
